1953;;Man in the Attic;;American;;Hugo Fregonese;;Jack Palance, Constance Smith;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Man_in_the_Attic;;The story takes place in London, 1888. On the third night of the Jack the Ripper killings, a man rents out an attic from an older couple in need of extra income. The man (Jack Palance), a research pathologist, begins working on his experiments in the rooms. Helen Harley, the landlady (Frances Bavier), becomes suspicious of the man, especially when her niece Lily Bonner (Constance Smith) shows an interest in him.